update.name: -CVE-2024-21683-RCE-in-Confluence-Data-Center-and-Server
update.description: This vulnerability allows an unauthenticated attacker to remotely execute arbitrary code on a vulnerable Confluence server. The vulnerability exists due to an improper validation of user-supplied input in the Confluence REST API. This allows an attacker to inject malicious code into the Confluence server, which can then be executed by the server
